{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n`CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID` is exposed as an env var ONLY in the remote/cloud runner; the LOCAL\nClaude Code CLI does not export it. Without a shim the session-provenance feature silently\nno-ops for local-CLI users — the most common case. The robust, harness-agnostic capture is a\nClaude Code SessionStart hook that reads the hook's `session_id` from stdin and exports it as\nthe portable `REBAR_SESSION_ID`, plus the harness tag `AI_AGENT=claude-code`.\n\n## What\n- **Hook script (`scripts/session-shims/claude-code-session-start.sh`).** Reads the\n  SessionStart JSON envelope from stdin (field `session_id`) and, when `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` is\n  set, APPENDS `export REBAR_SESSION_ID=<id>` and `export AI_AGENT=claude-code` to it. These\n  are the Claude Code hook-contract facts — the SessionStart stdin `session_id` field and the\n  `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` env-injection file — per the **Claude Code hooks reference**\n  (https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks), cited in the script header + docs page. GRACEFUL\n  DEGRADATION: this is the only external-API coupling, and if a future Claude Code renames the\n  field/var or changes the mechanism, the shim simply no-ops (no `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` / unparsed\n  `session_id` → exit 0) — it never errors or blocks the session, so a wrong assumption fails\n  safe. To make that fail-safe OBSERVABLE (not silently inert), the docs ship a **manual\n  verification procedure** (`echo \"$REBAR_SESSION_ID\"` in a fresh session; claim + `show` and\n  check `claimed_session`/`claim_harness`) so an operator can confirm the hook is actually\n  wired and diagnose an env-mechanism mismatch. This external-integration coupling is\n  irreducible — a shim MUST name the harness's env-injection var — and is grounded in the\n  cited official reference plus that verification step. The harness tag is the base name\n  `claude-code` (the `AI_AGENT` vocabulary permits an optional `_<version>` suffix, but the\n  local hook has no reliable version source, so it emits the bare base name). Uses `python3`\n  (already a rebar dependency) to parse the JSON\n  robustly — any parse failure, a missing/blank `session_id`, or an absent `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` is\n  a silent no-op with exit 0 (fire-and-forget; NEVER blocks the session). Idempotent: re-firing\n  on resume/clear/compact first STRIPS this hook's own prior `REBAR_SESSION_ID`/`AI_AGENT`\n  exports from the env file (preserving other hooks' lines) then re-writes the current values,\n  so the file never accumulates duplicate/stale lines and always reflects the CURRENT session\n  (whose id may differ across resume per gotcha G1 — not \"the same value\").\n- **Vocabulary alignment.** Update the `claude-code_<ver>` examples in `docs/config.md`,\n  `docs/event-schema.md`, and the `session_id.py` comment to present the harness tag as a base\n  name with an OPTIONAL `_<version>` suffix, so bare `claude-code` is consistent with the\n  documented vocabulary.\n- **Docs (`docs/session-id-shims.md`).** A new install guide: the `settings.json`\n  `hooks.SessionStart` snippet pointing at the script, the caveat that the id is NOT stable\n  across `--resume`/`--continue`/fork/subagents (epic gotcha G1 — treat it as \"the session\n  that emitted the claim event\"), and guidance to keep it session-scoped (do NOT export\n  `REBAR_SESSION_ID` from a shell profile — gotcha G3). Cross-links `docs/config.md`.\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the Claude Code SessionStart hook script; the `docs/session-id-shims.md` install page;\n  the small vocabulary-alignment edits (`docs/config.md`, `docs/event-schema.md`,\n  `session_id.py`) PLUS a matching update to the existing\n  `tests/unit/test_harness_provenance.py::test_docs_document_provenance` to assert the new\n  base-name form (see AC6); and a NEW `tests/unit/test_session_shims.py` validating the script\n  (valid shell + env-file output for mock stdin, malformed JSON, idempotent re-fire, and no-op\n  cases).\n- OUT: Codex/Cursor shims (S6 / 7656, which extend the same docs page); the record/read core\n  (S1-S3, S5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `scripts/session-shims/claude-code-session-start.sh` exists and is valid shell. Proof:\n      `bash -n scripts/session-shims/claude-code-session-start.sh` (asserted in\n      `tests/unit/test_session_shims.py`).\n- [ ] Given stdin `{\"session_id\":\"abc123\"}` and a `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` temp path, the script\n      writes `export REBAR_SESSION_ID=abc123` AND `export AI_AGENT=claude-code` to that file.\n      Proof: `pytest tests/unit/test_session_shims.py -k claude_code_exports -q`.\n- [ ] Robust no-op (exit 0, never blocks the session) for each of: a blank/missing\n      `session_id`, MALFORMED/unparseable JSON on stdin, an unset `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE`, AND an\n      UNWRITABLE `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` (path under a non-existent dir). Proof:\n      `pytest tests/unit/test_session_shims.py -k \"noop or malformed or unwritable\" -q`.\n- [ ] `docs/session-id-shims.md` includes a \"Verifying the hook is wired\" section (the\n      `echo \"$REBAR_SESSION_ID\"` + claim/`show` procedure), so the fail-safe design is\n      operator-observable. Proof: doc-content assert for \"Verifying the hook\".\n- [ ] Idempotent re-fire: firing twice with DIFFERENT `session_id`s leaves exactly ONE\n      `REBAR_SESSION_ID` export (the latest), one `AI_AGENT` export, and preserves a pre-existing\n      unrelated `export OTHER_HOOK_VAR=…` line (no accumulation, no stale id). Proof:\n      `pytest tests/unit/test_session_shims.py -k idempotent -q`.\n- [ ] `docs/session-id-shims.md` documents the hook script path + the `settings.json` install\n      snippet, and the two caveats by their specific phrasing. Proof: a doc-content assert in\n      `test_session_shims.py` checking `SessionStart`,\n      `scripts/session-shims/claude-code-session-start.sh`, the `\"hooks\"`/`\"SessionStart\"` JSON\n      snippet, and (whitespace-normalised) the exact G1 phrase \"NOT stable across `--resume` /\n      `--continue` / fork / subagents\" and the exact G3 phrase \"do NOT `export REBAR_SESSION_ID=…`\n      from a shell profile\".\n- [ ] The `claude-code_<ver>` vocabulary examples in `docs/config.md`, `docs/event-schema.md`,\n      and `session_id.py` are updated to a base-name + optional `_<version>` form, AND the\n      existing `test_harness_provenance.py::test_docs_document_provenance` is MODIFIED to add\n      two new assertions: `docs/config.md` no longer contains the old\n      ``claude-code_<ver>` / `opencode`` slash-form, and DOES contain ``base name `claude-code```.\n      The same base-name (not slash-form) change is applied to `docs/event-schema.md` and the\n      `session_id.py` comment. Proof: `pytest tests/unit/test_harness_provenance.py -k docs -q`\n      (now failing pre-edit, green post-edit).\n\n## Depends on\n- S1 (the `REBAR_SESSION_ID` contract) and S5 (the `AI_AGENT` -> `claim_harness` contract)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783550618162365001,"uuid":"2fa2b9f1-2eae-40a9-a9db-f194eb1d091b"}